                        All Army personnel are under AGIF insurance cover during their service period, which is a group insurance scheme. However, the insurance cover ceases after retirement
                        / discharge. Extended Army Insurance Scheme, which is also a group insurance, was started in 1981 against death for a specified period / prescribed age, whichever is earlier, for personnel retiring from service.
                        A single premium, at the rate decided from time to time by BOG, is retained out of the maturity benefit amount payable at the time of retirement / release / discharge, for this purpose.
                    </p>

