                    <p>
                        The Extended Insurance Scheme of AGIF is a compulsory group insurance scheme and all members on retirement/release/discharge (except DSC & TA) automatically become members of the scheme,
                        on payment of a one-time premium. The scheme, however, does not cover the following categories:
                    </p>

                    <div class="ms-4">
                        <div class="d-flex mb-2">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(a)</span>
                            <div>Individuals, who do not have adequate balance for recovery of single non-refundable / refundable premium at the time of retirement.</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="d-flex mb-2">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(b)</span>
                            <div>Deputationists from P & T Department who don't retired from Army.</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="d-flex mb-2">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(c)</span>
                            <div>Deserters.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

