                    <p>The details of documents required to be forwarded to AGIF by NOK to claim EI benefits:</p>

                    <div class="mb-3">
                        <h5 class="fw-bold">In case the claimant is Nominee or Contingent Nominee</h5>
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-3">
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                                <span class="fw-bold me-2">(i)</span>
                                <div>Extended Insurance (EI) certificate in original.</div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                                <span class="fw-bold me-2">(ii)</span>
                                <div>Death certificate of member (Veteran) with valid QR Scan Bar Code.</div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                                <span class="fw-bold me-2">(iii)</span>
                                <div>Cancelled cheque (or) 1st page of bank pass book copy of NOK (Claimant) with name of claimant printed on it.</div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                                <span class="fw-bold me-2">(iv)</span>
                                <div>Copies of AADHAR and PAN card of NOK (Claimant).</div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                                <span class="fw-bold me-2">(v)</span>
                                <div>Death certificate of Nominee with valid QR Scan Bar Code, if claimant is other than Nominee.</div>
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <h5 class="fw-bold">In case the claimant is other than Nominee or Contingent Nominee</h5>
                        <p>
                            The Extended Insurance (EI) amount will be distributed amongst remaining Class I legal heirs.
                            If none of the Class I legal heirs survive, then the amount may be claimed by Class II legal heirs. In case claimant is other than Nominee (or) Contingent Nominee, claim affidavit
                            <a href="../_forms/docu_insurance_claim/EI Affidavit.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm ms-2">Download Form</a> is required from
                            all beneficiaries in addition to the documents as mentioned above.
                        </p>

                        <h5 class="fw-bold">Consent Certificate</h5>
                        <p>
                            If Nominee, Contingent Nominee and any of the Class I / Class II legal heir is willing to give their share to any of the particular Class I / II legal heir, a consent certificate on
                            affidavit <a href="../_forms/docu_insurance_claim/EI Consent certificate.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm ms-2">Download Form</a> can be submitted to AGIF.
                        </p>
                    </div>
